name: OS-GoldenHarvest
description:
Model merge using OS-Honey and Gold (v1) and backcrossing it with Honeydew.

https://civitai.com/models/74688/os-honey-and-gold
https://huggingface.co/BakingBeans/Honeydew/resolve/main/Models/Honeydew.safetensors

This merge is made to give a more realistic style to Honey and Gold, while it looses a bit of its magic feel, it gains more control and keeps the beautiful landscapes,

this is a bit heavier of a model (~4gb) but it is much more versatile and requires less/no negative prompting compared to the H&G v1 and v2 models.

this model has more of a "realistic" anime style,
if you feel you are getting grayish/gloomy images, that can maybe be fixed using a vae, or using (blurry:1.5-2.0) in the negative prompt(idk why this works). this happens sometimes because honeydew does not have a VAE Baked into it.
